          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "And, for what was perhaps the highlight of the tour, we stopped for a lunch break at Fort Augustus, a small town on the southern shore of Loch Ness. Fun Fact: Loch Ness is twenty-three miles long and seven hundred feet deep, making it the largest loch in Scotland by volume."
